Ah, now I understand the issue! The navigation works (tabs switch correctly), but the footer content gets messed up when using the Next button from Database to Appendices. The footer shows database content instead of the normal footer text.

This is likely because there's an element with id="database" that's being targeted incorrectly, or there's a JavaScript function that's modifying the footer content. Let me provide a targeted fix:

Add this code right before the closing </script> tag (around line 5500-5600), after all your existing JavaScript:

```javascript
// FIX: Prevent footer corruption when navigating between tabs
// This ensures the footer content stays intact

// Store the original footer content
const footerElement = document.querySelector('footer');
const originalFooterHTML = footerElement ? footerElement.innerHTML : '';

// Override the switchTab function to protect the footer
const originalSwitchTab = switchTab;
switchTab = function(tabId) {
    // Call the original function
    originalSwitchTab(tabId);
    
    // Restore footer content after tab switch
    setTimeout(() => {
        if (footerElement) {
            // Check if footer has been corrupted (contains database content)
            if (footerElement.innerHTML.includes('species') || 
                footerElement.innerHTML.includes('filter') ||
                footerElement.innerHTML.includes('database')) {
                // Restore original footer
                footerElement.innerHTML = originalFooterHTML;
            }
        }
    }, 10);
};

// Also add a mutation observer to watch for footer changes
if (footerElement) {
    const observer = new MutationObserver(function(mutations) {
        mutations.forEach(function(mutation) {
            if (mutation.type === 'childList' || mutation.type === 'characterData') {
                // If footer content changed to something that looks like database content
                if (footerElement.innerHTML.includes('species') && 
                    !footerElement.innerHTML.includes('Student Learning Guide')) {
                    footerElement.innerHTML = originalFooterHTML;
                }
            }
        });
    });
    
    observer.observe(footerElement, { 
        childList: true, 
        characterData: true, 
        subtree: true 
    });
}

// Add click handler protection for the specific buttons
document.getElementById('nextToAppendices')?.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    // Schedule footer check after the tab switch
    setTimeout(() => {
        if (footerElement && footerElement.innerHTML.includes('species')) {
            footerElement.innerHTML = originalFooterHTML;
        }
    }, 50);
});

document.getElementById('nextToGlossary')?.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    setTimeout(() => {
        if (footerElement && footerElement.innerHTML.includes('species')) {
            footerElement.innerHTML = originalFooterHTML;
        }
    }, 50);
});
```

This fix:

1. Stores the original footer content when the page loads
2. Wraps the switchTab function to restore the footer after tab switching
3. Adds a MutationObserver that watches for footer changes and corrects them
4. Specifically targets the problematic navigation buttons (Database → Appendices and Appendices → Glossary)

The fix is non-invasive - it works alongside your existing code without breaking anything else, and only activates when the footer gets corrupted.
